  "text": "Bladder cancer (BC) patients are characterized by heterogenic prognostics due to variation in their extent of disease as illustrated by the division into non-muscle invasive (NMIBC)/TaT1CIS, muscle invasive bladder cancer (MIBC)/T2-T4 and metastatic BC. Great interest and effort has been put into understanding health-related quality of life and symptomatic issues affecting the overall QoL for MIBC patients having undergone surgical procedures [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Little is to the authors' knowledge known of the BC patients undergoing medical oncological treatment.",
